Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.69,0:01:46.73,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I can't find the will to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.31,0:01:48.48,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.81,0:01:51.54,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,There should be plenty to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.46,0:02:01.50,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,She only needed to be\N an apprentice as a pretense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.88,0:02:07.85,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,So I bought her without much thought, and \NI observed her without much thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.01,0:02:11.01,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think I'd need to do much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.10,0:02:14.79,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,She was quite unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:18.73,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,and she was surprisingly quick to warm up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:21.73,Magus-Internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.17,0:02:28.38,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't speak much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:35.40,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing her that way, I'm filled \Nwith two indescribable sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.20,0:02:42.37,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.05,0:02:48.44,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.62,0:02:53.35,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,It's done?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.14,0:03:01.15,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Is it done?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.95,0:03:03.03,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.40,0:03:06.44,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's add the final touches.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.99,0:03:12.71,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,You become sleepy because you've \Nunknowingly been using your magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.00,0:03:16.83,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,The things we make are imbued with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:22.18,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Ainsworth should have \Ntaught you these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.39,0:03:25.00,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I can't ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.87,0:03:27.85,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like giving him trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.49,0:03:34.22,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Taking care of youngsters \Ndoesn't even count as trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.22,0:03:37.38,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,You have no idea how much of \Na pain in the ass he's been.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:41.40,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Years went by, but he still was terrible\N at skiing, his soup was always burnt,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.40,0:03:45.32,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,he never learned to restrain himself, and \Nhe could never handle fire adequately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.75,0:03:48.72,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,You're far more deft and quick to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:50.33,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,What is that bonehead even...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.35,0:03:55.08,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, with your hair and this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.24,0:03:57.42,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Gems?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.77,0:04:00.71,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,I was given these by an \Nacquaintance a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.01,0:04:03.34,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,These stones are said to have been bathing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.34,0:04:06.72,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,in sunlight and moonlight for a thousand \Nyears at the bottom of a lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:08.86,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,They're shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:13.47,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,It's dim, but it ought to be enough to \Nlight the ground beneath your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:45.26,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,I took the liberty of wrapping \Nit around the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:48.53,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,It has a beautiful sunset color, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.84,0:05:50.81,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,This is your wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.14,0:05:52.81,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Take good care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.40,0:05:56.44,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:14.89,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.85,0:06:21.19,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, little mage. It has been some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.21,0:06:22.27,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:32.20,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for turning my \Nbranch into your wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.68,0:06:35.67,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.89,0:06:39.65,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.07,0:06:41.17,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:48.35,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Because we've established a bond\N of fate through the wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.79,0:06:50.35,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,A bond of fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:56.24,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,We're at the border between travelers \Nand those whose travels have ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.50,0:06:59.98,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Those on the other side \Nand those on this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.41,0:07:04.87,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Those whose paths never \Nmeet can intersect here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.75,0:07:08.47,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,So this is how it appears to your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:10.53,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful path.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.26,0:07:14.10,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Does it appear differently to your eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.59,0:07:17.08,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,I am already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:20.45,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,I depend on the vision \Nof your excellent eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.87,0:07:29.96,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,You always appear unhappy, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.74,0:07:33.30,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.69,0:07:38.10,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,All that's here is an old geezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.10,0:07:41.07,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try talking\Nto yourself out loud?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.75,0:07:54.37,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I've become greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:08:00.07,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I was content knowing I might \Nget kicked out at any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.11,0:08:03.45,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,So I tried not to depend on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.57,0:08:08.96,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I was comfortable, because \NI knew he thought nothing of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.47,0:08:14.62,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Because he called me family, \Neven if it was only for show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:17.50,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at some point, it began to upset me \Nthat he—Elias—wouldn't talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.10,0:08:28.36,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I became lonely and scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:37.05,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why I couldn't stay distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.88,0:08:40.98,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,That way, I wouldn't have had to be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:45.32,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I could have given up, no matter \Nwhen he'd thrown me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:52.16,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,I realize it's tasteless of me to respond \Nwhen you're just talking to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.80,0:09:02.26,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,But is your Elias someone who \Nwould suddenly throw you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.90,0:09:06.73,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Has he said such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.63,0:09:12.77,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Has anything happened, even \Nonce, to give you cause for worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:14.13,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.60,0:09:20.15,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Then you need to stop worrying \Nas though the sky is falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.15,0:09:24.15,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,But he might change his mind, \Neven if he's okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.51,0:09:27.66,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,He might get bored of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:29.49,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Just like she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.99,0:09:31.83,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Once he doesn't need me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.23,0:09:39.54,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I speak aloud to myself, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.32,0:09:46.02,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thankful to Chise's mother and father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.42,0:09:54.78,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,When a creature is struggling to survive, \Nit often abandons or kills its young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:59.96,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,If it can stay alive, it can\Nhave another child someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.92,0:10:06.30,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Chise's mother released \Nher hands off of her neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:08.50,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:15.29,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Why did she not kill Chise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.60,0:10:20.97,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Why did she kill herself instead, despite \Nwishing she hadn't given birth to Chise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:24.74,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.47,0:10:33.93,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Because Chise came to see me, I spent \Nmy last moments flying through the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.26,0:10:39.69,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,There were people and creatures \Nthat were saved by Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.34,0:10:44.94,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,A child was saved because \NChise called them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.16,0:10:54.29,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,To value oneself so little,\N as though one were disposable,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:11:00.84,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,is to say that those of us they've \Nsaved are just as worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:01.83,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,That's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.02,0:11:05.19,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.51,0:11:10.01,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't even trying to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.10,0:11:13.11,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Be that as it may,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.61,0:11:19.49,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,there are times when a simple word spoken \Nor a hand offered saves another.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.91,0:11:25.08,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,So I find myself wanting you \Nto be proud of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.27,0:11:31.04,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,You yourself, because you were able \Nto offer your hand to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.46,0:11:39.09,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,And I thank your mother and \Nfather for leaving you with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:41.79,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Nevin...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.16,0:11:45.55,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,You said my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.55,0:11:47.03,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.57,0:11:50.62,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lovely name given to me by Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.27,0:11:53.81,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori Chise,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:58.53,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,you are free.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.86,0:12:10.07,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you should be burdened by a curse \Nand eventually fall, that, too, is your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:18.03,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I want you to think—not for \Nanother—but about what {\i1}you{\i0} want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:26.61,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,That wand is my wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:30.93,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,No matter where you are, \Nit will light your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:35.01,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,You can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.53,0:12:39.72,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Myself, Lindel, even that child of thorns...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.72,0:12:46.70,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is connected, and all will return \Nhere to set forth on a new journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.78,0:12:48.83,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Nevin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.44,0:12:51.81,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a brief farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.76,0:12:59.68,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right, you should be quick to \Nsay what you wish to say or hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:07.69,Default,Zombie Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Some words ripen with age,\Nbut some also lose their color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.25,0:13:10.09,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.19,0:13:12.17,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:14.52,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:15.58,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.99,0:13:20.33,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I met with Nevin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:22.27,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,With Nevin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.33,0:13:28.04,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the wand and shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.47,0:13:31.12,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I have to return home right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:32.29,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.67,0:13:34.66,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to thank you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.10,0:13:38.06,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind, but what's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.71,0:13:50.29,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to tell Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:59.22,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make the best of the \Nencouragement he gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:00.61,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:02.98,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call Gwee.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:06.95,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:07.79,Default,Doug,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.86,0:14:13.42,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.13,0:14:17.25,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:18.49,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.97,0:14:39.85,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.29,0:14:42.86,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Connect me to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.18,0:14:46.23,Default,Burning,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.58,0:14:47.85,Default,Flaming,0000,0000,0000,,We're flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.96,0:14:59.43,Default,Burning,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.43,0:15:00.68,Default,Flaming,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:03.07,Default,Burning,0000,0000,0000,,Let's fly there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.43,0:15:07.04,Default,Burning,0000,0000,0000,,The wings of flame will \Ntake us around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.81,0:15:09.97,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,On these wings...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.07,0:15:39.42,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.76,0:15:45.08,Default,Grampa,0000,0000,0000,,I thought she was a quiet girl, but \Nshe might actually be a wolverine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:40.63,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.34,0:17:46.74,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to come home the way you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.74,0:17:48.13,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,but the fairies were...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.13,0:17:51.33,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I... I mean, my wand's finished, \Nso I wanted to come home early.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.64,0:17:54.36,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,So I got their help and used magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.36,0:17:57.65,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,See? Lindel-san finished it for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.70,0:18:04.91,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are pretty reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:12.35,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:17.65,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home, Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.64,0:18:22.08,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.34,0:18:25.64,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea how far \Nthe land of dragons is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:28.92,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You're an idiot to try to come by magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:29.75,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,An idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:32.88,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd be fine, \Nespecially with the wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:34.96,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Just get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.55,0:18:36.71,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.96,0:18:41.97,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.54,0:18:53.11,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:03.88,Magus-Flashback-internal,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.19,0:19:05.07,Magus-Flashback-internal,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.21,0:19:07.84,Magus-Flashback,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,There's a scary thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.18,0:19:09.36,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.31,0:19:12.28,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You can't let it scare you, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.57,0:19:14.94,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,The more scared you are, \Nthe more you'll attract.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.32,0:19:16.93,Magus-Flashback,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:19.21,Magus-Flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.21,0:19:20.77,Magus-Flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Dad will keep them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:26.10,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but you were \Nscared stiff at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.10,0:19:26.92,Magus-Flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:30.33,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're a big sister now,\NChise. You can handle it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:31.56,Magus-Flashback,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.34,0:19:36.49,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Good for you, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:38.69,Magus-Flashback-internal,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.26,0:19:44.27,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I was dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.25,0:19:49.69,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Mom wasn't crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.39,0:19:52.09,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't even angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.83,0:19:55.29,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot that had even happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.47,0:20:12.19,Default,Doug,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.77,0:20:14.57,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.83,0:20:16.32,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.68,0:20:18.73,Default,Doug,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.05,0:20:21.87,Default,Doug,0000,0000,0000,,They need to get lost. My urge \Nto chase them is rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.87,0:20:23.42,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:28.54,Default,Doug,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you had a good dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.11,0:20:29.86,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.48,0:20:36.54,Default,Space Scream,0000,0000,0000,,Stare...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:40.38,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Silky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.38,0:20:41.30,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.71,0:20:44.81,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.61,0:20:48.93,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.54,0:20:52.28,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Good thing you woke up in just two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.14,0:20:54.16,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.57,0:20:59.14,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's shearing season.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.49,0:21:05.72,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.69,0:21:19.31,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Until just recently, I could have never \Nimagined being in such a warm place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.19,0:21:35.94,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.82,0:21:40.86,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.03,0:21:51.86,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.68,0:21:53.78,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.84,0:22:07.93,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.77,0:24:01.76,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,The girl returns to the mage, \Nand the story begins anew.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:05.46,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,What does the visitor in \Nthe moonlit night bring?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.46,0:24:08.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is the master of the house available?
